_:Nf01ee945c1c64ce6984fb21ff74c36b1 <http://schema.org/articleBody> "<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Immigration Enforcement (IE) is the area of the Home Office responsible for preventing abuse of the immigration system, increasing compliance with immigration law, pursuing immigration offenders and protecting the vulnerable.</p>\n\n<p>IE works with partners across law enforcement, wider government, the private sector, and the voluntary sector to achieve this.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"vision\">Vision</h2>\n\n<p>Our people are world leaders at enforcing immigration law effectively and with integrity.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"missions\">Missions</h2>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p><b>Stop</b>: Prevent people from entering the UK illegally, ensure compliance and disrupt the organised crime groups</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><b>Manage</b>: Identify those in the UK without status, maintain contact with them and bring their cases to conclusion</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><b>Remove</b>: Remove those with no right to be here, especially high-harm individuals</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><b>Protect</b>: This underpinning mission recognises the vital role IE plays in protecting the UK public and economy, maintaining the integrity of the immigration system, and safeguarding vulnerable individuals</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"roles-and-responsibilities\">Roles and responsibilities</h2>\n\n<p>IE is a large and diverse operational organisation with staff based across the UK and internationally working in a wide range of different roles, including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>frontline enforcement officers who conduct enforcement visits to residential addresses and businesses suspected of engaging in illegal working</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>staff in reporting centres who manage face-to-face contact with illegal migrants, using meaningful conversations to explore their options on a case-by-case basis</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>caseworkers who make decisions on migrants’ cases, including foreign national offenders (FNOs), and progress their cases towards return from the UK where appropriate</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>a network of intelligence officers based overseas who work with international law enforcement partners to prevent harmful individuals from entering the UK</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>intelligence officers and criminal and financial investigators who investigate, disrupt and help to prosecute the organised crime groups (OCGs) involved in abusing the immigration system.</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n</div>" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
